The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Jan. 4: The shares of multiplex cinema operator PVR, which made its debut on bourses today, opened at an 18 per cent premium at Rs 260.35. The issue price was Rs 225. The scrip shot past the Rs-300-mark in early hours of trading due to hectic buying and trade in the region of Rs 305-Rs 310. The scrip hit a high of Rs 309.80 and a low of Rs 260.10 before closing at Rs 295.95 on BSE. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 4: Himachal Pradesh cadre IAS officer A.K. Mohapatra today assumed charges as the new shipping secretary. He was secretary to the ministry of parliamentary affairs before joining the shipping ministry.

 Chandigarh, Jan. 4: The RBI will issue new Rs 50 and Rs 100 denomination bank notes with inset letter L in both numbering panels in the Mahatma Gandhi series-2005.

 Mumbai, Jan. 4: Pidilite Industries today said its two wholly-owned subsidiaries in Singapore and Dubai have jointly incorporated a company in Bangladesh for manufacturing, trading and marketing activities.

 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The World Bank is helping the government put in place a viability gap funding for infrastructure, while planning to step up loan assistance to $3.35 billion annually in the coming years.




